title: Cambridge Environmental Chemistry Series [Updated 2016.10.01]
description:
Cambridge Environmental Chemistry Series

This wide-ranging series covers all areas of environmental chemistry, placing emphasis on both basic scientific and pollution-orientated aspects. It comprises a central core of text books, suitable for those taking courses in environmental sciences, ecology and chemistry, and provides comprehensive coverage at the undergraduate and first-year postgraduate level of atmospheric chemistry, chemical sedimentology, freshwater chemistry, marine chemistry and soil chemistry. At a more advanced level, the series contains topical accounts of current research interest.
